        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:13PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 312 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 10 miles south of Orogrande, moving southwest at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Orogrande and Oro Grande Range Complex.

This includes Highway 54 in New Mexico between mile markers 14 and
32.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
